00:11:19.920 --> 00:11:22.400 align:middle line:84%
the intrinsic systemic
problems that we

00:11:22.400 --> 00:11:26.510 align:middle line:84%
have in the fields of politics,
in the fields of finance,

00:11:26.510 --> 00:11:29.720 align:middle line:84%
in the fields of
business and bring us

00:11:29.720 --> 00:11:35.210 align:middle line:84%
to a more equitable system
where everyone can be happy?

00:11:35.210 --> 00:11:38.560 align:middle line:84%
>>GRIFFIN: I think that that
question is so important

00:11:38.560 --> 00:11:41.760 align:middle line:84%
that it needs to be broken
down a little bit, at least

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:44.200 align:middle line:90%
into two categories.

00:11:44.200 --> 00:11:49.250 align:middle line:84%
The first category is having to
do with what needs to be done.

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:51.490 align:middle line:84%
When people say how do you
solve this problem, what

00:11:51.490 --> 00:11:55.850 align:middle line:84%
they're usually thinking
of is, well, what do we do?

00:11:55.850 --> 00:11:58.940 align:middle line:84%
We need, for example--
of what needs to be done,

00:11:58.940 --> 00:12:04.060 align:middle line:84%
we need to restore the nation
to a sound monetary system.

00:12:04.060 --> 00:12:06.900 align:middle line:84%
We need to abolish
the Federal Reserve.

00:12:06.900 --> 00:12:10.840 align:middle line:84%
We need to do a lot
of things, and nobody

00:12:10.840 --> 00:12:13.430 align:middle line:84%
will disagree on
most of these things,

00:12:13.430 --> 00:12:15.440 align:middle line:90%
but that's the first category.

00:12:15.440 --> 00:12:17.820 align:middle line:84%
The second category
is, well, how?

00:12:17.820 --> 00:12:20.070 align:middle line:84%
It's easy to say we need
to do this, this, and this.

00:12:20.070 --> 00:12:22.070 align:middle line:84%
We get letters to the
editor all the time

00:12:22.070 --> 00:12:23.806 align:middle line:84%
